'''Charles K. Smith''' (February 15, 1799 &ndash; September 28, 1866) was an [[United States|American]] politician, lawyer, and first secretary of [[Minnesota Territory]].

Born in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]], he moved with his family to [[Hamilton, Ohio]]. Smith worked in the banking business and practiced law. Smith served as assisant county judge of Hamilton County. He was appointed the first secretary of [[Minnesota Territory]] serving 1849-1851. He also founded the [[Minnesota Historical Society]]. He then moved back to Hamilton, Ohio to practice law until his death.<ref>[http://www.rootsweb.com/~ohbutler/cyc/160.htm A History and Cyclopaedia of Butler County, Ohio]</ref> 

